# CODEOWNERS — risk-tier merge gate
#
# Paths listed here require @ckrhehfl's review before merge (enforced by
# branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" on main). This is
# the structural boundary between auto-mergeable and human-approval-required
# changes — see CLAUDE.md "Branch and Merge / Auto-merge Policy".
#
# Anything NOT matched below has no required reviewer: CI + CodeRabbit
# passing is sufficient for auto-merge. Keep this file's boundaries in sync
# with .coderabbit.yaml's path_instructions — same risk classification,
# two different enforcement mechanisms (advisory review vs. hard merge gate).

# Java Trading Plane: OMS / Risk Gateway / Execution / ExchangeAdapter /
# Reconciliation / Kill Switch — all execution and risk-affecting code.
/java/               @ckrhehfl

# Shared Python/Java contract schemas — breaking changes ripple into the
# Java trading plane.
/schemas/             @ckrhehfl

# Runtime config: leverage, risk/loss limits, live-trading flags.
/configs/             @ckrhehfl

# CI/CD workflows — modifying these is equivalent to code execution with
# repo secrets; a classic supply-chain attack surface.
/.github/             @ckrhehfl

# Governance/policy files themselves.
/CLAUDE.md            @ckrhehfl
/.coderabbit.yaml     @ckrhehfl
